1197→\section{Two Algebraic Structures}
1198→\label{sec:two_structures}
1199→%======================================================================
1200→
1201→The sBootstrap particle content and mass spectrum are constrained by
1202→two \emph{independent} algebraic structures.  Part~A
1203→(\S\ref{subsec:so32_chain}--\ref{subsec:so32_open}) derives the
1204→representation content from an $SO(32)$ embedding.  Part~B
1205→(\S\ref{subsec:casimir_eq}--\ref{subsec:casimir_open}) derives an
1206→electroweak mass ratio from a Casimir eigenvalue equation.
1207→No algebraic connection between the two has been found
1208→(see \S\ref{subsec:two_gap}).
1209→
1210→%----------------------------------------------------------------------
1211→\subsection{Part A: The SO(32) embedding chain}
1212→\label{subsec:so32_chain}
1213→%----------------------------------------------------------------------
1214→
1215→The $SO(32)$ gauge group of Type~I / heterotic string theory
1216→admits the maximal-subgroup chain
1217→\begin{equation}
1218→\label{eq:so32_chain}
1219→SO(32) \;\supset\; SU(16) \times U(1)_A
1220→  \;\supset\; SU(5) \times SU(3) \times U(1)_A \times U(1)_B \,.
1221→\end{equation}
1222→The first step is the standard embedding $SO(2n) \supset SU(n)
1223→\times U(1)$; the second decomposes $SU(16)$ under the regular
1224→subalgebra $SU(5) \times SU(3) \times U(1)_B$.
1225→Here $SU(5)$ is the Georgi--Glashow unification group and $SU(3)$
1226→is a \emph{horizontal} (flavor) symmetry acting on the three
1227→light generations---it is \textbf{not} $SU(3)_c$.
1228→
1229→The fundamental $\mathbf{32}$ of $SO(32)$ decomposes as
1230→\begin{equation}
1231→\label{eq:32decomp}
1232→\mathbf{32} = \underbrace{(\mathbf{5},\mathbf{3})}_{R_1}
1233→  \;\oplus\; \underbrace{(\bar{\mathbf{5}},\bar{\mathbf{3}})}_{R_2}
1234→  \;\oplus\; \underbrace{(\mathbf{1},\mathbf{1})}_{R_3}
1235→  \;\oplus\; \underbrace{(\mathbf{1},\mathbf{1})}_{R_4}\,,
1236→\end{equation}
1237→where $\dim = 15 + 15 + 1 + 1 = 32$ and the four summands carry
1238→distinct $U(1)_A \times U(1)_B$ charges.
1239→
1240→\subsection{Decomposition of the adjoint}
1241→\label{subsec:so32_adj}
1242→
1243→The adjoint of $SO(32)$ is the antisymmetric square of the
1244→fundamental: $\mathbf{496} = \wedge^2(\mathbf{32})$.  Distributing
1245→over the four summands in \eqref{eq:32decomp} and using the identity
1246→\begin{equation}
1247→\label{eq:wedge_product}
1248→\wedge^2(\mathbf{5},\mathbf{3})
1249→  = \bigl[\wedge^2(\mathbf{5}) \otimes S^2(\mathbf{3})\bigr]
1250→    \;\oplus\;
1251→    \bigl[S^2(\mathbf{5}) \otimes \wedge^2(\mathbf{3})\bigr]
1252→  = (\mathbf{10},\mathbf{6})
1253→    \;\oplus\;
1254→    (\mathbf{15},\bar{\mathbf{3}})\,,
1255→\end{equation}
1256→one obtains the full decomposition listed in
